    {
      "id": 19,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [-1600, 880],
      "size": [560, 360],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 6,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "title": "Usage",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": ["# FLUX 4K / 8K Hi-res Upscaler (load image)\n\n**Flow:** LoadImage -> 4x model upscale -> downscale to ~2MP (24GB-safe) -> FLUX img2img refine (denoise 0.35, adds real detail) -> final 4x model upscale -> exact 4K & 8K outputs.\n\n**Outputs:** `upscale_8K` (~33MP) and `upscale_4K` (~8.3MP). Mute the branch you don't need with Ctrl+B (select node 15+16 for 8K, or 17+18 for 4K).\n\n**Tuning:**\n- KSampler denoise 0.25-0.45 (higher = more invented detail, less faithful to source).\n- Swap UpscaleModelLoader to `RealESRGAN_x4plus.pth` for photos; `4x-UltraSharp.pth` is crisper for art/illustration.\n- FluxGuidance 2.5-3.5.\n- 8K refine is NOT done at full res (VRAM); refine runs at ~2MP, final 8K is a sharp lanczos resize of the 4x output. For true 8K-native detail use a tiled upscaler (Ultimate SD Upscale).\n\n**Models used:** flux1-dev.safetensors (fp8_e4m3fn) + clip_l + t5xxl_fp8_e4m3fn + ae.safetensors."],
      "color": "#222",
      "bgcolor": "#000"
    }
